I am so humbled and honored to have host Governor Phil Murphy, and so many dignitaries, for the historic and landmark signing of a statewide law I called for to deter burglaries & home invasions. This law makes home invasions & burglaries a 1st and 2nd degree crime, respectively with up to 20 years of a prison sentence for those age 15 and up. I fundamentally believe in social justice and balancing for socio economic disparities but it doesn‚Äôt change the fact that there needs to be a strong deterrent against crime. This bold & tough law is effective immediately and will serve as a deterrent against burglaries. The previous law had more sympathy for perpetrators rather than justice for victims.

Thank you Governor Phil Murphy for giving me the pen used to sign this bill! When I started calling for this law over one year ago, few thought it was possible. Yet, here we are! We got it done! We changed the NJ law to one of the toughest in USA!
